[2;36m                    [0m           The fuzzer-triggered extraction process attempted to write a file using a path    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that includes “..[35m/[0m” segments, leading to a directory traversal scenario.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability type:                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           File Path Traversal.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Stack trace highlights:                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The exception originates in                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check`                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • It propagates through `checkFile`, `checkObj`, and `processFileOutputStartHook` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in the sanitizer.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The sanitizer hook is invoked by                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded`.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Upstream, `PackageParser.parseEntry` and `PackageParser.parseEntries` handle    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         archive entries.                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Important observations:                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The sanitizer intercepts file creation requests, indicating Tika is extracting  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         embedded documents to disk.                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The malicious entry path contains “..[35m/../[0m”, escaping the configured output      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         root.                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The harness [1m([0m`TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`[1m)[0m merely passes input to `TikaCLI`; it is   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         not the root cause.                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code areas for further investigation:                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Apache Tika’s `PackageParser` class [1m([0mmethods: `parseEntry`, `parseEntries`,     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `_parse`, `parse`[1m)[0m.                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • `TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` – how it determines output paths for    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         extracted files.                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • `TikaCLI` output processing [1m([0m`OutputType.process` and related file I/O[1m)[0m.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Integration of `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer: registration of hooks and         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         assumptions about safe paths.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer discovered a critical file path traversal vulnerability when Apache      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika’s CLI unpacker attempted to write embedded documents to the filesystem. A      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         proposed patch added `Paths`, `UUID` imports and introduced logic to strip          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         directory components, normalize output paths, prevent traversal outside the target  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         directory, and avoid filename collisions. When building after applying the patch,   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the compilation failed with an “illegal start of expression” error in               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI.java`, indicating a syntax or placement issue in the inserted code.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer-guided fuzz test triggered                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         while TikaCLI was extracting embedded files.                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace shows the sanitizer rejecting output paths that include `..[35m/[0m`  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         sequences. The failure originates in                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded`, called by the fuzzer harness [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in `TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`.                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The raw exception pinpoints a path traversal attempt via a deeply nested       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `..[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m` name.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The existing code wrote `name` directly into a `FileOutputStream` on disk      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         without sanitizing directory components.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The fuzzer harness code [1m([0m`TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`[1m)[0m is only exercising Tika’s    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         CLI logic and is not itself the root cause.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added imports at the top of `TikaCLI.java`:                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              · `import java.nio.file.Paths;`                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              · `import java.util.UUID;`                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Replaced the original extraction snippet [1m([0mwhich directly constructed a         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mFileOutputStream[0m[1m([0moutputFile[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m with steps to:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              a. Derive `safeName` via `[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1m([0mname[1m)[0m[1;35m.getFileName[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              b. Resolve and normalize `outputFile` under `outputDir`.                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              c. If normalization detects traversal, re-strip to base name.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              d. Append a random UUID prefix on name collisions.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              e. Ensure parent directories exist via `Files.createDirectories`.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              f. Print the extraction message using `safeName`.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              g. Open the output stream with `new [1;35mFileOutputStream[0m[1m([0m[1;35moutputFile.toFile[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m`.    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Build Result                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Maven compilation of the patched code halts with:                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `[1m[[0mERROR[1m][0m [33m...[0m TikaCLI.java:[1m[[0m[1;36m1140[0m,[1;36m9[0m[1m][0m illegal start of expression`                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The error suggests that one or more of the added lines [1m([0mor a misplaced brace[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lies outside a valid method or block, causing Java syntax to break.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Code Areas for Further Investigation                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The exact location in `TikaCLI.java` where the patch was inserted: verify      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         matching of opening/closing braces and method boundaries.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The `FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` inner class or method where                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `parseEmbedded` resides — ensure imports and code align with the class structure.   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Other parts of the CLI code that perform file output [1m([0me.g., directory creation [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         earlier in the method[1m)[0m to see if similar sanitization logic must be applied.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Impact on the CLI’s argument-parsing logic around output directories           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`--output` flags[1m)[0m, as normalization depends on a correct `outputDir` value.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Any formatting or duplicate imports introduced at the top of the file that may [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         conflict with existing declarations.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
